# React + TypeScript Rules

## Components
- Always use functional components with TypeScript
- Export named, not default
- Props must be explicitly typed with `interface`

## Hooks
- Custom hooks for all side effects and business logic
- Prefix: `use` + PascalCase noun (`useUserProfile`)

## Imports
- Use `import type` for type-only imports
- Group: React → third-party → local → types

## Anti-patterns to avoid
- No class components
- No `any` type
- No prop drilling more than 2 levels deep — use context or state manager
